42 (e) A person found guilty of violating this Code section shall be subject to a fine not to
43 exceed:
44 (1) For the first offense, $100.00;
45 (2) For the second offense, $250.00; and
46 (3) For a third or subsequent offense, $500.00."
47 SECTION 2.
48 Said article is further amended by revising Code Section 4-11-16, relating to penalties, as
49 follows:
50 "4-11-16.
51 (a) Except as otherwise provided in Code Section 4-11-10.1, 16-12-4, or 16-12-37, any
52 person violating any of the provisions of this article shall be guilty of a misdemeanor and
53 shall be punished as provided in Code Section 17-10-3; provided, however, that, if such
54 offense is committed by a corporation, such corporation shall be punished by a fine not to
55 exceed $1,000.00 for each such violation, community service of not less than 200 hours nor
56 more than 500 hours, or both.
57 (b) Each violation of this article shall constitute a separate offense."
58 SECTION 3.
59 All laws and parts of laws in conflict with this Act are repealed.
